## Upvote if it helps !
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- We iterate through left and right nodes until we get to a leaf.
    - We construct the string in the recursion. 
    - During the recursion, we add ```->``` before the value of the node **only if it's not the root**.
    - We add the string to the result only when we get to a leaf.  

# Code
```
class Solution(object):
    def binaryTreePaths(self, root):
        res = []

        def dfs(node, s):
            if s != "":
                s += "->"
            s += str(node.val)
            if not node.left and not node.right: res.append(s)
            if node.left: dfs(node.left, s)
            if node.right: dfs(node.right, s)
